# Login / Auth Pattern

## Layers

1. Edge/session refresh (proxy/middleware) for cookies
2. Provider auth (usually Supabase email/password)
3. App user mapping (role, org, stores)
4. Server guards on every sensitive action
5. Role-based post-login redirect

## UI

- Native form + `useActionState` or equivalent server action pattern
- Inline error text (not only toasts)
- Show/hide password, accessible labels
- Forgot/reset password routes when product needs them

## Redirects (ops products)

- Cashier / field role → operational surface (POS, tickets)
- Admin / manager → dashboard
- Unauthenticated → login; preserve safe return path when appropriate

## Never

Client-only “auth checks” as the sole protection. Always re-enforce on the server.
